<h2>FAQ</h2>
<h4>Why don’t clients have to log in?</h4>

<p>Because you programmatically provide us with their <code>client_id</code> we can already authenticate who is
  who. Therefore clients have to login only into their account with your app, and that's it.</p>

<h4>What happens when new clients are created?</h4>

<p>When you create a new client on your platform/website, this will automatically create a new
  <code>client_id</code>. Vicancy
  will pick this up, and assign a new widget to this new client.
</p>

<p>
  Bottom line: <strong>You don't have to take any action.</strong></p>

<h4>Can I help a client, when he’s stuck somewhere?</h4>

<p>Yes, of course. Just go to your reseller page, search for the relevant user and click
  "Show Vicancies" button to view their widget. Now you can easily see what's going on, and help them out.
</p>
<p>Of course you can also contact our support, in case that's easier:
  <a href="mailto:support@vicancy.com">support@vicancy.com</a></p>

<h4>What does a client see when he doesn’t have any videos yet?</h4>

<p>In case a client doesn't have any videos yet we'll give them some more info about Vicancy, and why it might be
  a great product for them.</p>

<p>Users can instantly order their first video, and get started right away.</p>
<h4>Will the widget influence page load times?</h4>

<p>No, it won't influence page load, and user won't notice any difference.</p>

<p>The javascript is loaded in a non-blocking asynchronous way. This basically means that vicancy is last in line
  to be loaded: first all other stuff on the page is rendered, and only then will our widget be loaded.</p>
